---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Join array value.
@lot:
- string $join = ', ', $filter = true
@example: |
  $array = Anemon::from([
      'foo' => 0,
      'bar' => 1,
      'baz' => 2,
      'qux' => 3
  ]);

  $A = $array('.');
  $B = $array('/');
@example-description: It is the same as [`join`][link:join] but it will filters out items with `null` and `false` value and items with key prefixed by an `_`.
@result: |
  $A = '0.1.2.3';
  $B = '0/1/2/3';
...